---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// TODO(content/legal): review this draft policy and add a contact email +
// effective date you're happy with. Placeholder values are marked below.
const CONTACT_EMAIL = 'hello@tomprotects.com'; // TODO: confirm
const UPDATED = 'June 2026'; // TODO: confirm
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy — TomProtects"
  description="How TomProtects handles the information you share — the free checker, the newsletter, and the audit intake form."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Privacy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/50">Last updated: {UPDATED}</p>

    <div class="post-content mt-8 space-y-5 text-ink/80">
      <p>
        TomProtects keeps this simple. I collect the least I need to run the free checker, send the newsletter, and
        scope reviews — and I don't sell your data to anyone.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink">The free email checker</h2>
      <p>
        When you run the checker, I look up <strong>public DNS records</strong> for the domain in your email address
        (SPF, DKIM, DMARC). I don't access your mailbox or any private data. Your email address is added to my mailing
        list (via Kit) so I can send your results and follow-up fix-it guidance. I don't store the report itself.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink">Newsletter signups</h2>
      <p>
        If you subscribe, your email address is stored in Kit (my email provider) and tagged by where you signed up so
        I can send relevant content. You can unsubscribe at any time using the link in any email.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink">The audit intake form</h2>
      <p>
        Details you share on the intake form (name, domain, platforms, and any notes) are stored in Kit and used solely
        to scope and deliver your review. I don't share them with third parties.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink">What I don't do</h2>
      <p>
        I don't store your data anywhere beyond Kit, I don't run third-party advertising trackers, and I don't sell or
        rent your information.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink">Your choices</h2>
      <p>
        You can unsubscribe or ask me to delete your information at any time — just email
        <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`} class="font-medium text-accent underline-offset-4 hover:underline">{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
